    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a genus containing around eight species of armored placental mammals native to Asia and Africa, characterized by having a body covered with broad overlapping horny scales; they curl themselves up into a ball when threatened.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
